03-2. 선형회귀 (Linear Regression)

Simple linear regression

\(f(x_i) = Y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1X_{i} + \epsilon_{i}, \ \ for \ i = 1,2, ..., n\)

- \(\small \epsilon_{i} \sim^{i.i.d} N(0, \sigma^2), \ \forall i\)
- \(\small Independency, \ Normality, \ Homoscedasticity\)

Parameter estimation

  • OLS estimation

\(\frac{\partial{SSE}}{\partial{\hat{\beta_0}}} = 0, \ \ \ \hat{\beta_0} = \overline{y} - \hat{\beta_1}\overline{x}\)

\(\frac{\partial{SSE}}{\partial{\hat{\beta_1}}} = 0,\ \ \ \hat{\beta_1} = \frac{\sum_i^n(x_i-\overline{x})(y_i-\overline{y})}{\sum_i^n(x_i-\overline{x})^2}\)



- \(\small \sum_i^n(x_i-\overline{x})(y_i-\overline{y}) = S_{xy}\)
- \(\small \sum_i^n(x_i-\overline{x})^2 = S_{xx}\)

Multiple linear regression

\(f(x_i) = Y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1X_{1i} + \beta_2X_{2i} + \epsilon_{i}, \ \ for \ i = 1,2, ..., n\)

- \(\small \epsilon_{i} \sim^{i.i.d} N(0, \sigma^2), \ \forall i\) - \(\small \beta^TX = \beta_0 + \beta_1X_{1i} + \beta_2X_{2i}\)

OLS of Multiple linear regression

\(\hat \beta = (X'X)X^{-1}Y\)
\(X\) = Feature matrix
\(Y\) = Target

03-3. 특성공학과 규제 (Feature engineering and regularization)

Regularization 목적

  • 과적합 방지
  • 모델 파라메터 수를 조정 (단순한 모델)

주로 사용하는 penalty parameters

  • Ridge (L2 Norm)
  • LASSO (L1 Norm, Least absolute shrinkage and selection operator)
  • Elastic net (L1 + L2 Norm)

How to effect on parameter estimation

https://soobarkbar.tistory.com/30

Overview of OLS

min\(SSE = \sum_{i = 1}^n(y_i - \hat y_i)^2\)

Ridge penalty

\(J(\beta) = min(SSE \ + \lambda\sum_{j = 1}^p\beta_j^2)\)

  • When \(λ=0\), there is no effect, equals to the normal OLS regression objective function
  • As \(λ → ∞\), the penalty becomes large and forces the coefficients toward zero.

    https://bradleyboehmke.github.io/HOML

LASSO penalty

\(J(\beta) = min(SSE \ + \lambda\sum_{j = 1}^p |\beta_j|)\)

https://bradleyboehmke.github.io/HOML

04-1. 로지스틱 회귀 (Logistic regression)

Why logistic regression

https://bradleyboehmke.github.io/HOML

Multiple logistic regression

  • Formula extend

    \(p(X) = \frac{e^{\beta_0+\beta_1X_1+...+\beta_pX_p}}{1+ e^{\beta_0+\beta_1X_1+...+\beta_pX_p}} = \frac{1}{1 + e^{-(\beta_0+\beta_1X_1+...+\beta_pX_p)}}\)


  • Logit transformation


    \(g(X) = ln[\frac{p(x)}{1-p(x)}] = \beta_0 + \beta_1X+...+\beta_pX_p\)

Logistic estimation

https://www.analyticsvidhya.com/blog/2015/11/beginners-guide-on-logistic-regression-in-r/

04-2 확률적 경사 하강법 (Stochastic gradient descent)

Derivatives of cost function of logistic regression

Let’s see the cases of cost function of logistic regression
This equation does not have a closed-form solution


\(J(\theta) = -\frac{1}{m}\sum_{i= 1}^m[y_ilog(h_\theta(x_i)) +(1-y_i)log(1- h_\theta(x_i))\)

where, \(h_\theta(x_i) = \frac{1}{1+e^{-\theta x}}, \ \ y \in {0, 1}\)


The concept of gradient descent (GD) algorithm

Gradient descent (GD) algorithm

  • Objective (cost) function =
    \(\small J(\theta) = \frac{1}{2m}\sum_{i = 1}^{m}(h_\theta(x_i) - y_i)^2\)
    \(\small =\frac{1}{2m}\sum_{i = 1}^{m}(y_i - h_\theta(x_i))^2\)

  • Parameter update :
    Repeat until convergence {

    \(\small \theta_j^{(n+1)} = \theta_j^{(n)} - \gamma \frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_j}J( \theta^{(n)})\)

    }

05-1. 결정트리

Structure

  • Decision tree for conditions to play tennis

    https://medium.com/@anshulraghav2222/decision-tree-classification-9390d6038ac8

Partitioning rule of classification case

  • Maximize the reduction in cross-entropy or the Gini index
    • Gini index: \(I_G=1-\sum_{j=1}^{c}p_j^2\), \(\small c\) is number of class
    • Entropy: \(Entropy(p_j) =-\sum_{j=1}^cp_jlog(p_j)\)
